name: African Wildcat
description: The African Wildcat is the ancestor of all domestic cats. They have existed for thousands of years, predating Ancient Egypt by over 1000 years.

name: Abyssinian
description: The Abyssinian cat breed is known for its ticked coat pattern and large, expressive eyes. They are active, social, and playful.

name: American Curl
description: American Curls are recognizable by their unique curled back ears. They are affectionate and good with families.

name: American Shorthair
description: American Shorthairs are known for their longevity, robust health, and good looks. They are friendly and sociable.

name: American Wirehair
description: The American Wirehair breed features a unique wire-coat texture. They are easygoing and adaptable.

name: Balinese
description: The Balinese cat is known for its long, silky coat and sapphire-blue eyes. They are intelligent, agile, and vocal.
